Returns true if all elements in the collection match the given predicate

        val data = arrayList("foo", "bar")
        assertTrue {
            data.all{it.length == 3}
        }
        assertNot {
            data.all{s -> s.startsWith("b")}
        }

contains


 <T> Boolean contains(item: T)

Checks if collection contains given item.

Method checks equality of the objects with T.equals method.
If collection implements java.util.AbstractCollection an overridden implementation of the contains
method will be used.

count


 <T> Int count()

Count the number of elements in collection.

If base collection implements Collection interface method Collection.size() will be used.
Otherwise, this method determines the count by iterating through the all items.

count


 <T> Int count(predicate: (T) -> Boolean)

Returns the number of items which match the given predicate

        val data = arrayList("foo", "bar")
        assertEquals(1, data.count{it.startsWith("b")})
        assertEquals(2, data.count{it.size == 3})

filter


 <T> Collection<T> filter(predicate: (T) -> Boolean)

Returns a new List containing all elements in this collection which match the given predicate

        val data = arrayList("foo", "bar")
        val foo = data.filter{it.startsWith("f")}
        assertTrue {
            foo.all{it.startsWith("f")}
        }
        assertEquals(1, foo.size)
        assertEquals(arrayList("foo"), foo)

filterNot


 <T> Collection<T> filterNot(predicate: (T) -> Boolean)

        val data = arrayList("foo", "bar")
        val foo = data.filterNot{it.startsWith("b")}

        assertTrue {
            foo.all{it.startsWith("f")}
        }
        assertEquals(1, foo.size)
        assertEquals(arrayList("foo"), foo)

        val foo = data.filterNotNull()

filterNotNullTo


 <T, C> C filterNotNullTo(result: C)

        val foo = data.filterNotNullTo(linkedList())

        assertEquals(2, foo.size)
        assertEquals(linkedList("foo", "bar"), foo)

        assertTrue {
            foo is LinkedList
        }

filterNotTo


 <T, C> C filterNotTo(result: C, predicate: (T) -> Boolean)

Returns a new collection containing all elements in this collection which do not match the given predicate

        val data = arrayList("foo", "bar")
        val foo = data.filterNotTo(linkedList()){it.startsWith("f")}

        assertTrue {
            foo.all{!it.startsWith("f")}
        }
        assertEquals(1, foo.size)
        assertEquals(linkedList("bar"), foo)

        assertTrue {
            foo is LinkedList
        }

find

        val x = data.find{it.startsWith("x")}
        assertNull(x)
        fails {
            x.sure()
        }

        f.sure()
        assertEquals("foo", f)

flatMap


 <T, R> Collection<R> flatMap(transform: (T) -> Collection<R>)

Returns the result of transforming each item in the collection to a one or more values which
are concatenated together into a single collection

        val data = arrayList("", "foo", "bar", "x", "")
        val characters = data.flatMap{ it.toCharList() }
        println("Got list of characters ${characters}")
        assertEquals(7, characters.size())
        val text = characters.join("")
        assertEquals("foobarx", text)

fold


 <T> T fold(initial: T, operation: (T, T) -> T)

Folds all the values from from left to right with the initial value to perform the operation on sequential pairs of values

        // lets calculate the sum of some numbers
        expect(10) {
            val numbers = arrayList(1, 2, 3, 4)
            numbers.fold(0){(it, it2) -> it + it2}
        }

        expect(0) {
            val numbers = arrayList()
            numbers.fold(0){(it, it2) -> it + it2}
        }

        // lets concatenate some strings
        expect("1234") {
            val numbers = arrayList(1, 2, 3, 4)
            numbers.map{it.toString()}.fold(""){(it, it2) -> it + it2}
        }

foldRight


 <T> T foldRight(initial: T, operation: (T, T) -> T)

Folds all the values from right to left with the initial value to perform the operation on sequential pairs of values

        expect("4321") {
            val numbers = arrayList(1, 2, 3, 4)
            numbers.map{it.toString()}.foldRight(""){(it, it2) -> it + it2}
        }

forEach


 <T> Unit forEach(operation: (T) -> Unit)

Performs the given operation on each element inside the collection

        val data = arrayList("foo", "bar")
        var count = 0
        data.forEach{ count += it.length }
        assertEquals(6, count)

groupBy


 <T, K> Map<K, List<T>> groupBy( [result: Map<K, List<T>>], toKey: (T) -> K)

Iterates through the collection performing the transformation on each element and using the result
as the key in a map to group elements by the result

        val words = arrayList("a", "ab", "abc", "def", "abcd")
        val byLength = words.groupBy{it.length}
        assertEquals(4, byLength.size())

        val l3 = byLength.getOrElse(3, {ArrayList()})
        assertEquals(2, l3.size)
